title: Why we hand-code websites instead of using page builders
excerpt: Page builders promise speed and deliver debt — bloated markup, plugin rot, and a site Google struggles to read. Here's the honest case for hand-coded websites, what they cost in 2026, and the three questions that tell you which one you actually need.
